---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'coverage-comparison', text: 'Coverage Comparison', level: 2 },
  { id: 'pricing', text: 'Pricing', level: 2 },
  { id: 'network-and-claims', text: 'Network and Claims', level: 2 },
  { id: 'who-should-choose', text: 'Who Should Choose Which', level: 2 },
  { id: 'verdict', text: 'Our Verdict', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'AXA Global Review', href: '/providers/axa-global' },
  { title: 'Cigna Global Review', href: '/providers/cigna-global' },
  { title: 'Best Expat Insurance', href: '/best/expat-health-insurance' },
  { title: 'France Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/france/insurance' },
  { title: 'Germany Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/germany/insurance' },
];

const coverageColumns = [
  { key: 'feature', header: 'Feature' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const coverageRows = [
  { feature: 'Inpatient Care', axa: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Outpatient Care', axa: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Mental Health', axa: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Maternity', axa: 'Optional', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Dental', axa: 'Optional', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Vision', axa: 'Optional', cigna: 'Optional' },
  { feature: 'Wellness Programs', axa: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'Medical Evacuation', axa: true, cigna: true },
  { feature: 'US Coverage', axa: 'Add-on', cigna: 'Add-on' },
  { feature: 'Annual Maximum', axa: '€1M-Unlimited', cigna: '$1M-Unlimited' },
];

const pricingColumns = [
  { key: 'profile', header: 'Profile' },
  { key: 'axa', header: 'AXA Global' },
  { key: 'cigna', header: 'Cigna Global' },
];

const pricingRows = [
  { profile: 'Single, Age 30', axa: '€110-150/mo', cigna: '$140-180/mo' },
  { profile: 'Single, Age 45', axa: '€180-240/mo', cigna: '$220-280/mo' },
  { profile: 'Couple, Age 35', axa: '€220-300/mo', cigna: '$280-360/mo' },
  { profile: 'Family of 4', axa: '€380-520/mo', cigna: '$450-600/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="AXA Global vs Cigna Global"
  description="Compare AXA Global and Cigna Global side by side. Coverage, pricing, and which international health insurance is right for you."
  headline="AXA Global vs Cigna Global: EU vs US Insurer Comparison"
  subheadline="Two global insurance giants with different regulatory backgrounds. Here's how they stack up for expats."
  heroBackgroundImage="/images/compare/axa-vs-cigna-hero-bg.png"
  heroImage="/images/pages/provider-card-generic.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Get Quotes from Both"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
    <h2 id="overview">Overview</h2>
  <p>
    AXA Global and Cigna Global are both popular choices for international health insurance, but they serve different needs. Understanding their key differences will help you choose the right coverage for your situation abroad.
  </p>
  <p>
    AXA Global is part of the French AXA group, offering robust international health plans. Their main strong presence in Europe and Asia with comprehensive plan options. They're particularly popular among expats in Europe and Asia who want a well-established provider, with competitive pricing with flexible deductible options.
  </p>
  <p>
    Cigna Global is known for its extensive global network and strong customer service. They're known for their massive provider network with direct billing at over 1.5 million healthcare facilities worldwide. They tend to attract families and American expats who prioritize convenience, offering premium pricing but many feel the convenience justifies the cost.
  </p>
  <p>
    This comparison breaks down the key differences between these two providers so you can make an informed decision. We'll cover coverage options, pricing estimates, network access, claims processes, and help you determine which one makes more sense for your specific needs and budget.
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">AXA Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>EU-regulated (stronger consumer protections)</li>
        <li>Strong European hospital networks</li>
        <li>Competitive pricing vs US insurers</li>
        <li>Good for EU-based expats</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Cigna Global</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>Largest global provider network</li>
        <li>Strong customer service reputation</li>
        <li>Better US coverage options</li>
        <li>More established brand globally</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Both Providers"
    description="Get quotes from AXA Global and Cigna Global for your situation."
    buttonText="Get Free Quotes"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="coverage-comparison">Coverage Comparison</h2>
  <p>
    Both insurers offer comprehensive international health coverage. The differences are subtle but can matter depending on where you live and what you prioritize.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={coverageColumns} rows={coverageRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Key differences:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Regulatory framework:</strong> AXA operates under EU insurance regulations, which include stronger consumer protections and complaint resolution processes</li>
    <li><strong>Currency:</strong> AXA quotes in euros, Cigna in dollars—this can affect costs depending on exchange rates</li>
    <li><strong>Network depth:</strong> Cigna has more direct-billing relationships globally; AXA is stronger in Europe</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="pricing">Pricing</h2>
  <p>
    AXA Global tends to be more competitively priced than Cigna, especially for European coverage. Here are estimated monthly premiums.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
  </div>

  <p>
    <strong>Notes on pricing:</strong>
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>AXA is typically 10-20% less expensive for similar coverage levels</li>
    <li>US coverage adds significant cost to both plans</li>
    <li>AXA's high-deductible options can reduce premiums substantially</li>
    <li>Currency fluctuations between EUR and USD can shift relative value</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Get Your Actual Price"
    description="Estimates vary. See what you'd actually pay based on your details."
    buttonText="Get a Quote"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <h2 id="network-and-claims">Network and Claims</h2>

  <h3>Provider Networks</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> has the larger global network with 1.5 million+ providers and strong direct-billing relationships worldwide.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA Global</strong> has excellent coverage in Europe and growing networks in Asia and the Americas. Direct billing is available at major hospitals but you may need to file for reimbursement more often outside Europe.
  </p>

  <h3>Claims Process</h3>
  <p>
    Both offer online claims submission. Cigna's portal is widely considered more polished. AXA's claims processing is reliable but can take slightly longer.
  </p>

  <h3>Regulatory Protections</h3>
  <p>
    AXA's EU regulation means you have access to EU insurance ombudsman services if disputes arise. Cigna, as a US company, operates under different regulatory frameworks depending on where you're covered.
  </p>

  <h2 id="who-should-choose">Who Should Choose Which</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose AXA Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You're living primarily in Europe</li>
        <li>You value EU consumer protections</li>
        <li>You want competitive pricing</li>
        <li>You prefer being billed in euros</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Choose Cigna Global If:</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You want the largest provider network</li>
        <li>You travel globally and need coverage everywhere</li>
        <li>Direct billing is important to you</li>
        <li>You may need US coverage</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="verdict">Our Verdict</h2>
  <p>
    Both AXA Global and Cigna Global are excellent international health insurers. The choice often comes down to geography and priorities.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>AXA Global</strong> is a strong choice for expats in Europe who want competitive pricing and the backing of EU regulations. It's also worth considering if you prefer doing business with a European company.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> makes more sense if you need extensive global coverage, prioritize direct billing, or want the reassurance of working with the largest international health insurer by network size.
  </p>
  <p>
    Get quotes from both to compare actual pricing for your situation—the premium difference might make the decision easier.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Decide?"
    description="Compare quotes from both providers based on your specific needs."
    buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This comparison is for informational purposes only. Prices, coverage, and plan details change. We are not insurance brokers. Verify all information with the providers before purchasing.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
